sin card
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a car dealer display card which provides details of a used car's age, price, and odometer reading, along with information about consumer law.
Origin:acronym
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:Commerce
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: acronym for Supplier Information Notice; replaced in 2008 by CIN card (Consumer Information Notice)
Citations
Date: 13/1/2007
Source: Dominion Post
Author:
Vol / Page: A7
Edition:
Quote: Ladies Mile Cars Ltd and its director, Sam Alsabiry, were fined $3140 in Auckland District Court for failing to attach sin cards to used motor vehicles .. He sent his customers sin cards created after the fact, and backdated forms for them to sign.
